reviews.review_text: Classic 85 Dead Can't beat a Touch opener and Tons of Steel..after all it is 1985...Second set Dear Mr. Fantasy-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat..woo-hoo..sure wish I was outside in BEAUTIFUL Southern California right now at this show rather than in fnt of the monitor workin' for the man...

Loud balloon pop that pop is not a balloon.It is a firecracker(m80)That went off by my friends foot.I was taping in the taping section and Skip and Robert were up front.I could hear it from the tapers section no problem.

Nice encore! Great to see an encore that wasn't Dayjob during this period. I remember going to the 11/1/05 Richmond show where they did Gloria, She Belongs to Me and other great tunes, just to be followed by a Dayjob encore. 

I remember laughing when they started it and walking out so I wouldn't ruin my experience that night! Kind of like having great sex and than when your done the girl tells you she has herpes!! Doooohhhh!!!

My turnaround show This is the one that got me officially "on the bus".  Although I had been going to concerts since '73 and always loved their music I had never traveled outside of Santa Barbara or Ventura to see my favorite band perform live.  A friend encouraged me to go to this show and it kicked ass as you can hear and from then on I never missed a show outside of California except for one in Eugene.  Nice job Mark, you done good.
